max Window bounds does not output the screen size
    System.out.print("MAX W: " + gr.getMaximumWindowBounds().width + ", ");
    System.out.println("MAX H: " + gr.getMaximumWindowBounds().height + ";");
but this does for both screens
    GraphicsDevice[] gs = GraphicsEnvironment.getLocalGraphicsEnvironment().getScreenDevices();
    for (int i = 0; i < gs.length; i++) {
        System.out.println(gs[i].getDisplayMode().getWidth() + " " + gs[i].getDisplayMode().getHeight());
    }

